FBIS3-5745 "dreas047_a_94016" FBIS-EAS-94-047 Document Type:Daily Report 10 Mar 1994 NORTHEAST ASIA Japan Police Arrest 106 Suspected Illegal Chinese OW1003010194 Tokyo KYODO in English 0048 GMT 10 Mar 94 OW1003010194 Tokyo KYODO Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Wakayama, March 10 KYODO -- Police rounded up a group of 106 Chinese early Thursday [10 March] in Susami, Wakayama Prefecture, on suspicion of illegally entering Japan. The Chinese had rented about 10 cars after landing in the coastal town aboard several small boats, and were apprehended while making their way to Osaka and Nagoya, police said. Police suspect there is a syndicate organization which plotted the entry attempt. In late November, a group of nearly 100 Chinese sneaked into the country through a tiny port some 10 kilometers northwest of Susami.
